data.content:
Yes! Use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType` to combine the cast and null check, and it gives a clearer failure message:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(factory.Create("email"));

    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` returns the cast object directly, so you can keep asserting on it — no manual cast or separate null check needed.
